d_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"1. Create a folder on Device A with byte-sized tiny files. In my test, I used 10,000 of < 10-byte files.\r\n2. Share the folder with Device B.\r\n3. While syncing, Device B displays `Syncing (100%, 0 B)`, even though the files are not `0 B`, and also not at `100%`.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5626656/104138262-44653900-53e6-11eb-8373-26cb4755ed5a.png)\r\n\r\nAlso, once the synchronisation has finished, the GUI on Device A is stuck in the following state, even though the actual folders are in sync. The glitch/error does go away after pausing and unpausing the folder on both devices.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/5626656/104138363-f13fb600-53e6-11eb-9384-81542c32bd64.png)\r\n\r\nNot sure how useful they are, but I also have logs from both devices with `STTRACE=db,model` enabled.\r\n\r\n[DeviceA-syncthing.log](https://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/files/5793496/DeviceA-syncthing.log)\r\n[DeviceA-syncthing.0.log](https://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/files/5793497/DeviceA-syncthing.0.log)\r\n[DeviceA-syncthing.1.log](https://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/files/5793498/DeviceA-syncthing.1.log)\r\n\r\n[DeviceB-syncthing.log](https://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/files/5793499/DeviceB-syncthing.log)\r\n[DeviceB-syncthing.0.log](https://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/files/5793500/DeviceB-syncthing.0.log)\r\n[DeviceB-syncthing.1.log](https://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/files/5793502/DeviceB-syncthing.1.log)\r\n[DeviceB-syncthing.2.log](https://github.com/syncthing/syncthing/files/5793503/DeviceB-syncthing.2.log)\r\n\r\nTested with Syncthing v1.12.1.","closed_by":{"login":"calmh","id":125426,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNTQyNg==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/125426?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/calmh","html_url":"https://github.com/calmh","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/calmh/followers","following_url":